From: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>
Date: Tue, 3 Sep 2024 02:49:06 +0100
Subject: testsuite: If validation result is not as expected, log the diff

It's easier to diagnose test failures if everything (within reason)
is in the build log.

Signed-off-by: Simon McVittie <smcv@debian.org>
Forwarded: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/-/merge_requests/7687
---
 testsuite/tools/validate.in | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/testsuite/tools/validate.in b/testsuite/tools/validate.in
index b3f1edd..d8a3301 100644
--- a/testsuite/tools/validate.in
+++ b/testsuite/tools/validate.in
@@ -32,6 +32,7 @@ for t in ${TESTS[*]}; do
     echo "ok $I $name"
     rm "$diff"
   else
+    sed -e 's/^/# /' < "$diff"
     echo "not ok $I $name"
     cp "$expected" "$ref"
   fi
